|Ronald J. McIntosh walked away from a minimum security prison on October 28 and then rented a helicopter on November 5.<ref name="NY_Times_1986">{{cite news |date=November 6, 1986|url = https://www.nytimes.com/1986/11/06/us/around-the-nation-woman-escapes-prison-in-a-hijacked-helicopter.html?n=Top/Reference/Times%20Topics/Subjects/H/Helicopters|title = Around the nation; Woman Escapes Prison In a Hijacked Helicopter|publisher = New York Times| accessdate = May 14, 2009 | last=[[United Press International]] |quote=}}</ref> He used the helicopter to free Samantha Lopez from the [[Federal Correctional Institution, Dublin|Federal Correctional Institution at Dublin]], east of San Francisco. Both were later caught on November 15 when they arrived to pick up wedding rings from a [[California]] shopping mall. The authorities were monitoring the account McIntosh used to write the check and the police were waiting for them.

Ron McIntosh for his role in the escape was sentenced to 25&nbsp;years in prison. Samantha Lopez was given five years added to her 50-year sentence for a 1981 bank robbery in Georgia.<ref name="pleasanton">{{cite news | date = July 19, 1987 | url = https://www.nytimes.com/1987/07/19/us/lovers-sentenced-in-escape-from-prison-in-a-helicopter.html?sec=&pagewanted=print | title =  Lovers Sentenced in Escape From Prison in a Helicopter | publisher = New York Times | accessdate = May 14, 2009}}</ref> As they were driven away to their separate prisons McIntosh was able to lean out of a car window and yell, "''I love you!"'' to Lopez.<ref name="NYT_I_Love_u">{{cite news |date=November 23, 1986|url = https://www.nytimes.com/1986/11/23/weekinreview/headliners-back-in-the-arms-of-the-law.html?sec=&spon=|title = Headliners; Back in the Arms of the Law|publisher = New York Times| accessdate = May 14, 2009 | last= |quote=}}</ref>  Samantha Lopez was released from prison on {{date|2010-04-20}}.<ref name="Federal_Bureau_of_Prisons">{{cite web |year=2009 |url = http://www.bop.gov/iloc2/InmateFinderServlet?Transaction=NameSearch&needingMoreList=false&FirstName=Samantha+&Middle=&LastName=Lopez&Race=U&Sex=U&Age=&x=68&y=9|title = Inmate Locator&nbsp;— Locate Federal inmates from 1982 to present|publisher = [[Federal Bureau of Prisons]]| accessdate = May 14, 2009 | last= |quote=}}</ref>
